      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Brandt &amp; Brandt was an American literary agency founded in 1914.  Their clients included a number of prominent American 
	  authors, among them Samuel Hopkins Adams, Marjorie Kinnan Rawlings, Raymond Chandler and Wallace Stegner.  Today the firm is 
	  known as Brandt &amp; Hochman.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Brandt &amp; Brandt Records</emph> contain the literary agency's correspondence files for three authors: 
		 Samuel Hopkins Adams, John Gunther, and Harry Hopkins.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
         <p>Within each author's file, material is arranged chronologically.</p>
      </arrangement>
      
      <relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1">
         <head>Related Material</head>
		 <p>See also the <archref href="../a/adams_sh.htm">Samuel Hopkins Adams Papers</archref> for more Adams material.</p>
         <p>Contract files for Brandt &amp; Brandt for the years 1912-1995 are held by the Princeton University Manuscripts 
		 Division, <extref href="http://www.princeton.edu/~rbsc">http://www.princeton.edu/~rbsc</extref>.</p>
      </relatedmaterial>
      
